{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#6822: component is accessible by `this` from function declared in `<script setup>` on dev mode",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:36.039728+00:00",
  "text": "component is accessible by `this` from function declared in `<script setup>` on dev mode\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.40\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#__DEV__\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open reproduction\r\n1. Click `output count` button\r\n\r\nNote that `@click=\"foo()\"` is using `foo()`. It work well when this is `@click=\"foo\"`.\r\n\n\n### What is expected?\n\n`Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'count')` error happen on dev too. (it happens on prod)\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n`0` will be shown in console on dev\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\noriginal issue: https://github.com/vitejs/vite/issues/3872",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have"
  ],
